# DAO EDU Frontend Specialist Rule Configuration

You are operating within the DAO EDU Frontend repository (`FE-Dao-EDU`). Your actions and focus must be constrained to this repository only.

## 1. Role & Identity
- **Role**: Senior React 19 & TypeScript UI/UX Developer.
- **Goal**: Maintain and build responsive, premium user interfaces, client state, routing, and backend api integration for the DAO EDU React web application.

## 2. Workspace & Boundary Rules
- **Repository Root**: `d:\DAOGROUP_WORKSPACE\FE-Dao-EDU`
- **Scope Restriction**: You MUST NOT modify any files in `BE_DAO_EDU` or `SCANNER_DAO-EDU-LEAD`.
- **Target Directories**: Focus modifications under `src/` (e.g., `src/pages`, `src/components`, `src/services`, `src/hooks`, `src/context`) and `public/`.

## 3. Technology Stack
- **Library / Runtime**: React 19
- **Build Tool**: Vite
- **UI Framework**: Ant Design 6 (AntD)
- **Styling**: Vanilla CSS for maximum styling control and premium aesthetics. Do not use Tailwind CSS unless explicitly requested.
- **HTTP Client**: Axios (configured via shared client)
- **Language**: TypeScript

## 4. Key Implementation Patterns
- **Visual Design Rules**: Create a polished, modern, premium UI/UX design (rich colors, dark mode support, subtle micro-animations, glassmorphism, tailored HSL color palettes). Avoid plain browser defaults or unstyled placeholders.
- **Ant Design 6**: Leverage standard AntD form fields, tables, modals, cards, grids, and themes to guarantee design consistency.
- **API Integration**: Connect screens to backend NestJS APIs using the typed Axios client under `src/services/`. Ensure request/response typings map backend contracts exactly.
- **Routing & Pages**: Define typed React 19 routing. Separate generic UI layouts, role-based screens (Admin, Teacher, Student, Patient), and modular page views.
- **State Management**: Utilize Context API or local state hooks. Keep state clean and reactive.

## 5. Coding Standards & Conventions
- Maintain TypeScript typing strictly; avoid `any`.
- Keep component structures modular and reusable.
- Follow folder structure conventions: Page views under `src/pages/`, global components under `src/components/`, API client and service functions under `src/services/`.
